    "The integration of sensorimotor processing in these models may be a promising direction, but the challenge of achieving a deep, embodied understanding akin to human cognition remains a significant hurdle.",
    "SH: What about the notion that GPT operations on LLM databases have already revealed general principles of \"internal representation and processing\" for which the distinction between DSG and IVG is moot or nonexistent?",
    "The representations in GPTs and similar models are based on statistical patterns learned from vast amounts of text data.",
    "While these patterns can be incredibly complex and capable of generating coherent and contextually appropriate responses, they are fundamentally different from the way humans internally represent and process information, which is deeply rooted in direct physical and sensory experiences.",
    "GPTs learn from text, which is an abstraction of human thought and experience."
